  "response_text": "# Simple Vegetable Curry\n\n## Ingredients\n- 2 tbsp oil or ghee\n- 1 onion, diced\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tbsp ginger, minced\n- 2 tbsp curry powder (or paste)\n- 1 can (14 oz) coconut milk\n- 1 cup vegetable broth\n- 2 cups mixed vegetables (bell peppers, carrots, zucchini, peas, potatoes)\n- 1 can (14 oz) diced tomatoes\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Fresh cilantro (optional)\n\n## Instructions\n\n1. **Sauté aromatics**: Heat oil in a large pot. Cook onion for 3-4 minutes until softened. Add garlic and ginger, cook 1 minute.\n\n2. **Toast spices**: Stir in curry powder and cook for 1 minute until fragrant.\n\n3. **Add liquids**: Pour in coconut milk and broth, stirring well.\n\n4. **Add vegetables**: Add harder vegetables first (potatoes, carrots). Simmer 10 minutes, then add softer ones (peppers, zucchini).\n\n5. **Simmer**: Add tomatoes and simmer 15-20 minutes until vegetables are tender.\n\n6. **Season**: Taste and adjust salt, pepper, and spice level.\n\n7. **Serve**: Garnish with cilantro and serve over rice or with naan bread.\n\n**Cook time: ~35 minutes | Serves: 4**",
